commit.message:
Support using SDL_audiolib with -fno-exceptions (#32)

When SDL_audiolib is included as a subproject and the parent project 
disables C++ exceptions, it fails to build due to a throw in the 
SdlMutex constructor.

Fix it by simply moving the constructor to its own source file and 
always build it with exceptions enabled.

commit.message:
Fix infinite loop in SDL audio callback

When a stream doesn't have a resampler and the decoder's total samples
are less then the output buffer size, the decoding loop in the audio
callback would never exit because callAgain was initialized to true and
it could never become false.

verification.payload:
tree 6d87f4577cb0d57bff27de3011ef71a92aaaad63
parent 7a53959569ab29a1e883a8acaac061745cdb557c
author Nikos Chantziaras <realnc@gmail.com> 1651308923 +0300
committer Nikos Chantziaras <realnc@gmail.com> 1651308923 +0300

Fix infinite loop in SDL audio callback

When a stream doesn't have a resampler and the decoder's total samples
are less then the output buffer size, the decoding loop in the audio
callback would never exit because callAgain was initialized to true and
it could never become false.

commit.message:
Fix lib and pkgconfig install location

It's not specified whether CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR a relative path or not.
CMake is supposed to do some magic with it depending on how you use it,
but clearly that's not always working. The lib suffix might be wrong
(like "lib32" instead of "lib", or "lib" instead of "lib64") or on some
systems we get something silly like "/usr/local/usr/local/lib" when
combined with CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX. See:

https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=795542

The GNUInstallDirs module defines CMAKE_INSTALL_FULL_LIBDIR, which is
guaranteed to be absolute. So just use that instead.

verification.payload:
tree 38fb2f234bafa5f2daf628ee090a90a3617a1222
parent ff8bd4cb8d80599b167d5b150412e5decdf552ee
author Nikos Chantziaras <realnc@gmail.com> 1650164242 +0300
committer Nikos Chantziaras <realnc@gmail.com> 1650164242 +0300

Fix lib and pkgconfig install location

It's not specified whether CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR a relative path or not.
CMake is supposed to do some magic with it depending on how you use it,
but clearly that's not always working. The lib suffix might be wrong
(like "lib32" instead of "lib", or "lib" instead of "lib64") or on some
systems we get something silly like "/usr/local/usr/local/lib" when
combined with CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX. See:

https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=795542

The GNUInstallDirs module defines CMAKE_INSTALL_FULL_LIBDIR, which is
guaranteed to be absolute. So just use that instead.
